## IV. Submission Instructions

- **Two PDF volumes:** (1) Technical & Past Performance, (2) Price.
- **Page numbers required on all pages.**
- **Submission via email** to: james.postell@va.gov (5MB max/attachment).
- **SAM Registration and UEI required.**
- **Acknowledge all amendments.**
- **Include safety procedures (written).**

---

## V. Compliance & Insurance

- **Standard minimum coverage per FAR 28.307-2, 52.228-5**:
  - Workers’ Compensation
  - General Liability
  - Work on Government Installation
  - Additional coverage per contract Section C.3
- **Safety program required; quarterly VA inspections.**
- **Government provides:** Utilities, grease trap/fire suppression maintenance, trash.
- **Contractor provides:** All food operations, staff, dietary compliance, cleaning.

---

## VI. Qualification/Disqualification Criteria

**QUALIFIERS:**
- Located in the United States (Hawaii).
- Fits EVS/dietary/food operational scope.
- No clinical/medical care required.
- Ample proposal window (>2 weeks).
- Insurance requirements are standard.
- No union mandate or specialized assets required.
- Contract value expected >$250K/year.

**DISQUALIFIERS:**
- Not registered in SAM/UEI.
- Incomplete submission or missing safety program.
- Failure to acknowledge amendments.
- Unacceptable insurance or safety program.
- Non-compliance with instructions.

